, "updated_at": "2018-07-31T17:35:11Z", "closed_at": "2018-07-31T17:35:11Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/21212", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21212", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21212.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21212.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>The epoch loss that's calculated in the current notebook is a bit inaccurate.</p>\n<p>It is currently calculated as <code>total_loss/len(input_tensor)</code>. But the <code>total_loss</code> is already averaged across a batch. So, for <code>epoch loss</code> calculation, <code>total_loss</code> needs to be divided by the number of batches instead of total number of examples.</p>\n<p>This PR adds code to calculate total number of batches <code>N_BATCH</code> and then calculate the epoch loss as <code>total_loss/N_BATCH</code>.</p>\n<p><a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=43051\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/lamberta\">@lamberta</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=14262417\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/yashk2810\">@yashk2810</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=17151892\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/tensorflower-gardener\">@tensorflower-gardener</a></p>", "body_text": "The epoch loss that's calculated in the current notebook is a bit inaccurate.\nIt is currently calculated as total_loss/len(input_tensor). But the total_loss is already averaged across a batch. So, for epoch loss calculation, total_loss needs to be divided by the number of batches instead of total number of examples.\nThis PR adds code to calculate total number of batches N_BATCH and then calculate the epoch loss as total_loss/N_BATCH.\n@lamberta @yashk2810 @tensorflower-gardener", "body": "The epoch loss that's calculated in the current notebook is a bit inaccurate.\r\n\r\nIt is currently calculated as `total_loss/len(input_tensor)`. But the `total_loss` is already averaged across a batch. So, for `epoch loss` calculation, `total_loss` needs to be divided by the number of batches instead of total number of examples.\r\n\r\nThis PR adds code to calculate total number of batches `N_BATCH` and then calculate the epoch loss as `total_loss/N_BATCH`.\r\n\r\n@lamberta @yashk2810 @tensorflower-gardener "}